    "caption": "Loud, bold, brilliant blue, and extremely aware of everything happening.",
    "shortDescription": "Blue jays are the neighborhood alarm system — when a hawk appears, they scream a warning and every small bird nearby freezes or hides. They're also excellent mimics and can copy a red-tailed hawk's cry so well that other birds scatter even when there's no hawk in sight. Fun fact: Blue jays bury thousands of acorns every autumn and remember where most of them are buried."
